      "id": 1,
      "name": "good_prompt",
      "prompt": "You are an empathetic HR Manager at a tech startup. Write a rejection email to a candidate who reached the final interview stage but was not selected. Maintain a professional yet warm tone, provide constructive feedback on their coding test, and encourage them to apply for future roles.",
      "response": "Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nWe appreciate the time you took to participate in our final interview for the [Position] role. We were impressed by your skills and experience, but after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose skills and fit were a better match for the position at this time.\n\nYour coding test demonstrated strong problem-solving abilities, and we were particularly impressed with your approach to [specific area of coding]. However, we felt that your code did not quite meet the complexity and scalability requirements of the role.\n\nWe encourage you to continue developing your skills and applying for future opportunities that align with your strengths. We appreciate your interest in our company and wish you the best in your job search.\n\nSincerely,\n[Your Name]\nHR Manager",
